title: Jeff Phelps '71 Oral History Interview for the Georgia Dental Project
description: Jeff Phelps, a 1973 Grinnell College graduate, discusses his involvement in the college's concert program, particularly as North Lounge coordinator. He highlights Georgia's crucial role in organizing concerts, including securing bands like The Jackson Five and Jefferson Airplane. He shares personal anecdotes about the community's reaction to concerts and the impact of Georgia's booking skills. Jeff emphasizes Georgia's influence on his love for live music and her significant contributions to the college's cultural scene.

title: Rob Killion '90 Oral History Interview for the Georgia Dental Project
description: Rob Killion is an alumnus of Grinnell College from 1990 and former SGA Vice President. This interview discusses his involvement with the removal of Georgia Dentel from student concerts bookings during his tenure on SGA, as well as other milestone events in Grinnell's history in his time. These include the same-sex kiss-in over Melanie Colley's petition to live off campus with her lesbian partner, a black student forum, and a few memorable bands.
